  "question_id": "41242532-3b2f-48ba-9d77-1368a284cc51",
  "short_text": "Rectangle",
  "content": "Write a program that reads two numbers `M` and `N`, and prints a **Rectangle** of `M` rows and `N` columns using stars (`*`).\n\n```\n*****\n*****\n*****\n*****\n```\n\n---\n\n#### Input\n\nThe first line of input contains an integer representing `M`.\nThe second line of input contains an integer representing `N`.\n\n---\n\n#### Output\n\nThe output should be `M` rows and `N` columns containing stars (`*`) as a **Rectangle** shown in the sample output.\n\n---\n\n#### Explanation\n\nFor example, if the given numbers are `M = 4` and `N = 5`,\n\n- Print the stars (`*`) on **4** rows and **5** columns as shown in the given image.\n\n<Img imageSrc='https://assets.ccbp.in/frontend/content/programming-foundations/rectangle.png' widthPercent='70'/>\n\nThe output should be,\n\n```\n*****\n*****\n*****\n*****\n```\n",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "e9ef177e-a06f-468a-b6c9-4098e48fae68",
      "code_content": "rows = int(input())\ncolumns = int(input())\n\ncounter = 0\nwhile counter < rows:\n    print(\"*\" * columns)\n    counter = counter + 1",
      "language": "PYTHON",
      "default_code": true
    }
  ],
